\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Class balance in \texttt {master\_with\_features.csv}. The analysed pilot subset is balanced across the human class and the four LLM classes represented in the feature table.}}{12}{figure.1}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Best binary mean F1-score by feature set and model. Combined and syntactic feature sets dominate the strongest human-versus-model comparisons, especially for Gemma and Llama.}}{13}{figure.2}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Mean binary F1-score by feature set and estimator across the saved binary tasks. Horizontal layout keeps all feature-family labels readable.}}{14}{figure.3}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Fold-level F1-score distribution across binary feature sets and estimators. Lexical and stanza configurations are generally weaker and less reliable than the strongest combined and syntactic settings.}}{15}{figure.4}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Multiclass mean macro-F1 by feature set and estimator. Combined and syntactic configurations are clearly stronger than lexical, writeprints, stylometrix, and stanza-based alternatives.}}{16}{figure.5}%
